2
00:00:39.984 --> 00:00:42.215
Mrs. Landry. you're
looking lovely as ever.

3
00:00:42.419 --> 00:00:45.218
Jimmy McGill.

4
00:00:45.389 --> 00:00:46.516
What are you doing here?

5
00:00:46.690 --> 00:00:48.591
I was in the area.
and I thought:

6
00:00:48.792 --> 00:00:51.227
"I wonder how my favorite
former client is doing."

7
00:00:51.395 --> 00:00:52.829
And I have cookies.

8
00:00:53.030 --> 00:00:55.727
Oh. you're so sweet. Come on in.

9
00:00:55.900 --> 00:00:58.301
After I made these.
I looked down...

10
00:00:58.502 --> 00:01:02.769
and I thought "Wow. that
looks just like your Felix."

11
00:01:02.940 --> 00:01:05.034
They do.

12
00:01:05.209 --> 00:01:08.441
- You're so thoughtful.
- Well. I was afraid you wouldn't be here.

13
00:01:08.612 --> 00:01:12.515
Thought with that settlement money.
you might've moved somewhere swankier.

14
00:01:12.716 --> 00:01:14.116
What do you mean?

15
00:01:14.318 --> 00:01:15.911
The settlement.

16
00:01:16.086 --> 00:01:17.418
The Sandpiper case?

17
00:01:17.588 --> 00:01:19.750
- That's gotta be wrapped up by now.
- Oh. that.

18
00:01:19.924 --> 00:01:23.224
That... That... That's
still years away.

19
00:01:23.394 --> 00:01:26.228
- You haven't settled?
- No. I don't know all the details yet...

20
00:01:26.430 --> 00:01:30.891
but Erin... Uh. Erin Brill of
Davis & Main. do you know her?

21
00:01:31.068 --> 00:01:35.597
Lovely girl. She reminds
me of a young Mary Martin.

22
00:01:35.773 --> 00:01:40.939
Oh. yes. I... I have met her. Just
a... She's a wonderful young lady.

23
00:01:41.111 --> 00:01:42.773
Well. she takes
care of all that...

24
00:01:42.980 --> 00:01:45.643
and she said there's
still a long way to go.

25
00:01:45.883 --> 00:01:48.250
But you've received
an offer. right?

26
00:01:48.419 --> 00:01:51.446
Something sent
to you in writing.

27
00:01:51.622 --> 00:01:54.114
I mean. something more
than just Erin and you chatting?

28
00:01:54.358 --> 00:01:55.485
Oh.

29
00:01:59.163 --> 00:02:01.962
It's probably all
here in this box.

30
00:02:02.132 --> 00:02:07.127
I can't make heads or tails of
it. but you are welcome to look.

31
00:02:07.304 --> 00:02:08.431
You sure?

32
00:02:08.606 --> 00:02:11.576
Of course. It's you.

33
00:02:12.743 --> 00:02:15.372
Well. uh. I gotta say...

34
00:02:16.313 --> 00:02:21.013
I can't blame you for getting
mixed up with all this. Heh.

35
00:02:21.318 --> 00:02:25.949
I mean. these legal notices. I mean.
no one really understands them.

36
00:02:26.156 --> 00:02:28.682
You know. I've got a law degree.

37
00:02:28.892 --> 00:02:31.157
Sometimes. I can't even. uh...

38
00:02:35.032 --> 00:02:37.126
I can't even. uh...

39
00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:44.706
You haven't. uh...

40
00:02:45.342 --> 00:02:46.833
accepted this?

41
00:02:47.044 --> 00:02:49.809
Erin says we should wait.

42
00:02:50.314 --> 00:02:51.782
But...

43
00:02:53.450 --> 00:02:55.885
Erin doesn't really
matter. does she?

44
00:02:56.053 --> 00:02:59.182
I mean. you're the
class representative.

45
00:02:59.456 --> 00:03:00.719
That's a big deal.

46
00:03:00.924 --> 00:03:04.554
That means you. and
you alone. decide. You're...

47
00:03:04.728 --> 00:03:08.824
You are the legal stand-in
for your friends and neighbors.

48
00:03:08.999 --> 00:03:13.664
I don't know about all that. Jimmy. I
just leave it all to the professionals.

49
00:03:14.538 --> 00:03:18.134
Yeah. Sure. sure.
Lawyers know best.

50
00:03:18.842 --> 00:03:20.333
But I'm sorry...

51
00:03:20.511 --> 00:03:23.538
if you won the lottery. I mean.
you'd take the lump sum. right?

52
00:03:23.714 --> 00:03:26.377
I mean. money now is
better than money later.

53
00:03:27.017 --> 00:03:29.350
- Bird in the hand?
- I suppose.

54
00:03:29.553 --> 00:03:32.022
More time to enjoy it.

55
00:03:33.057 --> 00:03:34.889
You really should talk to Erin.

56
00:03:35.059 --> 00:03:37.858
She knows all the ins and outs.

57
00:03:38.028 --> 00:03:41.556
Ins and outs. Yeah. Erin
sure knows those. Heh.

58
00:03:42.066 --> 00:03:45.332
I'd be happy to
talk to Erin. Uh...

59
00:03:45.736 --> 00:03:50.071
But I just can't help but wonder
if she's taking every aspect into...

60
00:03:52.042 --> 00:03:53.442
Oh. Jimmy.

61
00:03:53.610 --> 00:03:57.672
I completely forgot. I'm
on my way to chair yoga.

62
00:03:57.848 --> 00:03:59.680
I'm so sorry.

63
00:03:59.850 --> 00:04:01.580
Oh. it's okay. Um...

64
00:04:01.752 --> 00:04:06.213
I probably should be
going. I have a lot to do.

65
00:04:10.994 --> 00:04:12.223
Jimmy.

66
00:04:12.429 --> 00:04:15.263
- Jimmy.
- Rose. Myrtle. Helen.

67
00:04:15.432 --> 00:04:17.697
That chair yoga
really works. huh?

68
00:04:17.868 --> 00:04:19.302
You all look 10 years younger.

69
00:04:19.536 --> 00:04:22.904
- Oh. you honeydripper.
- Hey. hurry up. It starts in five minutes.

70
00:04:23.073 --> 00:04:26.043
- You wanna come with us?
- You're welcome to. We can have guests.

71
00:04:26.243 --> 00:04:29.702
I would love to. uh.
but I'm not dressed for it.

72
00:04:29.880 --> 00:04:32.076
So I'll take a rain check.

73
00:04:32.249 --> 00:04:34.718
Certainly. Thanks for
the cookies. Jimmy.

74
00:04:34.918 --> 00:04:36.443
Bye.

75
00:04:41.558 --> 00:04:43.117
That can't be right.

76
00:04:43.293 --> 00:04:45.421
Can't be right.

77
00:04:48.966 --> 00:04:52.528
Seventeen point four total.

78
00:04:52.770 --> 00:04:54.602
Thirty-three percent
is the common fund.

79
00:04:54.772 --> 00:04:57.742
So I'm one-fifteenth.

80
00:04:57.908 --> 00:04:59.536
Fifteen into 17...

81
00:05:01.678 --> 00:05:03.647
Carry the two...

82
00:05:04.148 --> 00:05:07.482
One million. one
hundred and sixty.

83
00:05:08.418 --> 00:05:13.823
One million. one hundred
and sixty thousand.

84
00:05:14.291 --> 00:05:16.760
Heh. Holy shit.

85
00:05:52.863 --> 00:05:54.195
- Mr. Ehrmantraut?
- Yes.

86
00:05:54.398 --> 00:05:57.300
Sorry to keep you waiting.
It'll be right this way.

87
00:05:58.101 --> 00:06:00.627
Can I get you anything to
drink? Tea. water. espresso?

88
00:06:00.804 --> 00:06:03.501
No. I'm fine. Thank you.

89
00:06:19.523 --> 00:06:22.083
- Ms. Rodarte-Quayle. I have your next...
- Yes. thank you.

90
00:06:22.259 --> 00:06:24.524
Mr. Ehrmantraut.
Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

91
00:06:24.695 --> 00:06:25.695
Mike.

92
00:06:25.863 --> 00:06:27.331
Thanks. Justin.

93
00:06:27.497 --> 00:06:30.057
Have a seat. Um...

94
00:06:30.234 --> 00:06:31.668
Mike...

95
00:06:31.835 --> 00:06:36.830
HR sent up your start paperwork.
I-9. W-2. pretty standard.

96
00:06:38.675 --> 00:06:41.770
Could I have your driver's
license and Social Security card?

97
00:06:42.246 --> 00:06:45.683
- Why?
- My assistant needs to make a copy.

98
00:06:46.350 --> 00:06:50.082
How does this hire work.
exactly? Walk me through it.

99
00:06:50.254 --> 00:06:54.282
You'll receive a paycheck from Madrigal
in the amount of $10.000 per week.

100
00:06:54.458 --> 00:06:58.623
I believe at that rate. your employment
should be paid out in about 20 weeks.

101
00:06:58.795 --> 00:07:02.357
Mr. Fring has arranged to
cover FICA. Social Security...

102
00:07:02.532 --> 00:07:04.433
the entirety of the tax burden.

103
00:07:04.601 --> 00:07:06.433
I assume that's
all right with you?

104
00:07:09.306 --> 00:07:13.402
Good. So to that end. I have you
down as a "logistics consultant."

105
00:07:13.577 --> 00:07:14.670
What is that?

106
00:07:15.112 --> 00:07:18.446
It's a person who
consults on logistics.

107
00:07:18.615 --> 00:07:20.447
Does it matter?

108
00:07:21.084 --> 00:07:23.815
I'm not long on logistics.

109
00:07:23.987 --> 00:07:27.754
"Security consultant" would
be better. I used to be a cop.

110
00:07:28.258 --> 00:07:32.457
That'll look better on work history than
your current employer. SMQ Parking.

111
00:07:32.629 --> 00:07:33.756
So...

112
00:07:33.931 --> 00:07:35.763
you take my money...

113
00:07:35.933 --> 00:07:38.334
run it through this joint.
and it's clean? That it?

114
00:07:38.502 --> 00:07:40.061
Yes.

115
00:07:40.504 --> 00:07:42.063
Who knows this operation?

116
00:07:42.239 --> 00:07:44.265
You? Anyone else?

117
00:07:44.441 --> 00:07:47.001
- No.
- You sure?

118
00:07:47.744 --> 00:07:51.408
May I ask what. precisely.
is your concern here?

119
00:07:51.615 --> 00:07:56.781
I'm concerned about what happens
if you put my real name in your books.

120
00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:59.615
Your Madrigal is a
German company.

121
00:07:59.790 --> 00:08:02.589
One thing I know about
Germans is they love a good audit.

122
00:08:05.128 --> 00:08:08.462
I oversee eight freight terminals
across Texas and the Southwest.

123
00:08:08.632 --> 00:08:13.969
Operating costs range between
$800.000 and $1 million per week.

124
00:08:14.338 --> 00:08:17.706
All due respect.
Mike. but your money?

125
00:08:17.874 --> 00:08:19.433
It's a rounding error.

126
00:08:19.609 --> 00:08:21.771
If the IRS or
anyone else looks...

127
00:08:21.945 --> 00:08:24.123
you're a contractor for a
multinational corporation...

128
00:08:24.147 --> 00:08:27.276
with 114.000
employees worldwide.

129
00:08:27.451 --> 00:08:29.682
You're like every other
person in this building.

130
00:08:30.053 --> 00:08:32.147
Like you?

131
00:08:32.956 --> 00:08:35.118
You think I'm not on the books?

132
00:08:35.292 --> 00:08:36.555
I am.

133
00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:37.887
Under my own name.

134
00:08:38.061 --> 00:08:40.895
- This is the way you handled it before?
- Handled what?

135
00:08:41.064 --> 00:08:44.000
The money for
Fring's other guys.

136
00:08:44.968 --> 00:08:46.903
Other guys?

137
00:08:47.537 --> 00:08:49.904
This is the first
time I've done this...

138
00:08:50.073 --> 00:08:51.871
for anyone.

139
00:08:52.876 --> 00:08:54.970
I don't know what you do. but...

140
00:08:55.345 --> 00:08:58.281
Mr. Fring must think
you're quite good at it.

141
00:09:14.097 --> 00:09:15.565
Twenty weeks.

142
00:09:15.799 --> 00:09:17.734
The sooner you're off
my books. the better.

143
00:09:17.901 --> 00:09:19.836
Justin?

144
00:09:26.943 --> 00:09:30.038
Can you make a copy of
these. please? Thank you.

145
00:09:33.316 --> 00:09:36.309
- Hmm.
- What?

146
00:09:38.388 --> 00:09:41.017
This is a very nice office.

147
00:09:41.224 --> 00:09:43.056
Thank you.

148
00:09:45.862 --> 00:09:48.422
Seem to be risking a
lot for a drug dealer.

149
00:09:49.332 --> 00:09:51.130
Drug dealer?

150
00:09:55.072 --> 00:09:57.701
If that's all you think he is...

151
00:09:58.542 --> 00:10:00.477
then you don't
know Gustavo Fring.

152
00:10:20.363 --> 00:10:22.229
Let me understand you.

153
00:10:22.399 --> 00:10:28.168
You're proposing to double our premiums
on every one of our practicing attorneys?

154
00:10:28.505 --> 00:10:32.169
We know this is abrupt.
New issues have come to light.

155
00:10:32.375 --> 00:10:34.310
New issues?

156
00:10:34.478 --> 00:10:36.447
You mean Mr. McGill's
testimony at the bar?

157
00:10:36.613 --> 00:10:37.911
That's a part of it. Yes.

158
00:10:38.115 --> 00:10:42.246
After 25 years of paying full premiums.
I can count on one hand our claims.

159
00:10:42.419 --> 00:10:45.878
This is an underwriting decision.
You shouldn't take it personally.

160
00:10:46.089 --> 00:10:49.321
In some special circumstances. we
have been known to extend a rider.

161
00:10:49.493 --> 00:10:50.688
What kind of rider?

162
00:10:50.894 --> 00:10:54.661
A senior. management-level partner
who would supervise Charles' work.

163
00:10:54.831 --> 00:10:56.959
Attend court and client
meetings with him...

164
00:10:57.400 --> 00:10:58.629
review filings.

165
00:10:58.802 --> 00:11:02.432
We've done this for clients with a
high probability of health failure...

166
00:11:02.606 --> 00:11:04.726
As a precaution
What you're saying is...

167
00:11:04.841 --> 00:11:08.141
for any case Charles takes on.
another partner is tied up as well.

168
00:11:08.311 --> 00:11:09.836
And we don't bill a penny more?

169
00:11:10.013 --> 00:11:11.481
This is ludicrous.

170
00:11:11.681 --> 00:11:14.116
The insurance industry
is heavily regulated.

171
00:11:14.284 --> 00:11:16.810
I can think of a dozen infractions
here off the top of my head.

172
00:11:16.987 --> 00:11:18.182
Mr. McGill.

173
00:11:18.421 --> 00:11:20.788
You're hoping we'll
either find another carrier...

174
00:11:20.957 --> 00:11:23.517
or cut you an enormous
check. Win-win for you.

175
00:11:23.727 --> 00:11:26.026
I assure you. neither
is going to happen.

176
00:11:26.229 --> 00:11:27.697
What will happen is very simple:

177
00:11:27.864 --> 00:11:30.800
You're going to do right by us.
or we will compel you to do so.

178
00:11:30.967 --> 00:11:33.732
- What do you mean by "compel"?
- You know exactly what I mean.

179
00:11:33.970 --> 00:11:36.235
If you're threatening
litigation. this meeting is over.

180
00:11:36.439 --> 00:11:38.135
Then it's over.

181
00:11:39.176 --> 00:11:40.508
Thank you for your time.

182
00:11:40.677 --> 00:11:43.579
Mr. Hamlin. Mr. McGill.

183
00:11:53.356 --> 00:11:55.325
All right. Where do we start?

184
00:11:55.492 --> 00:11:57.654
Francis should start
digging into regulations.

185
00:11:57.827 --> 00:12:01.559
I'm sorry. I don't have the code
sections at my fingertips just now.

186
00:12:01.731 --> 00:12:03.427
Let's pull a team
of associates...

187
00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:07.059
and get them looking at
every angle of injunctive relief.

188
00:12:07.237 --> 00:12:09.502
Before close of business.
we'll hit Santa Rosa...

189
00:12:09.673 --> 00:12:13.166
with a demand letter
that'll make their heads spin.

190
00:12:13.343 --> 00:12:16.336
Odds are. inside a week.
they'll be sitting at the table again.

191
00:12:16.513 --> 00:12:19.073
And if not. well...

192
00:12:19.249 --> 00:12:21.775
we've never shied
away from a fight.

193
00:12:25.188 --> 00:12:26.781
Chuck. do you
remember Al McConnell?

194
00:12:26.990 --> 00:12:28.754
Of course. Hell of a litigator.

195
00:12:28.992 --> 00:12:32.429
- Retired now. isn't he?
- He's a professor at UNM now.

196
00:12:32.596 --> 00:12:35.430
Wrote a fantastic book on
SCOTUS during Reconstruction.

197
00:12:35.599 --> 00:12:36.726
Fascinating stuff.

198
00:12:36.933 --> 00:12:38.561
- Okay.
- I was talking to him...

199
00:12:39.402 --> 00:12:43.601
and he mentioned he'd love
you to come speak to his One-L's.

200
00:12:43.773 --> 00:12:46.072
Maybe make it a regular
thing. if you wanted.

201
00:12:48.044 --> 00:12:49.979
What are you talking
about. Howard?

202
00:12:50.146 --> 00:12:51.978
What I'm saying is...

203
00:12:52.148 --> 00:12:55.050
maybe it's time to
hang up your spurs.

204
00:12:55.719 --> 00:12:57.153
Become partner emeritus.

205
00:12:57.320 --> 00:12:59.755
Leave your name on the
firm. but focus on your legacy.

206
00:12:59.923 --> 00:13:03.382
You always said you wanted to
work on the Commerce Clause.

207
00:13:03.560 --> 00:13:05.324
You can write the book on it.

208
00:13:05.528 --> 00:13:07.588
And no longer be
a practicing lawyer.

209
00:13:10.166 --> 00:13:11.964
Chuck. there's
more to life than this.

210
00:13:12.602 --> 00:13:15.128
That day is far in
the future. Howard...

211
00:13:15.305 --> 00:13:18.537
and I don't appreciate
the suggestion.

212
00:13:19.843 --> 00:13:22.677
- What if it's not a suggestion?
- Meaning?

213
00:13:22.846 --> 00:13:25.611
Meaning if enough people
tell you that you're drunk...

214
00:13:25.782 --> 00:13:28.047
maybe it's time to sit down.

215
00:13:30.620 --> 00:13:33.180
You want me to retire over this?

216
00:13:33.356 --> 00:13:35.621
- The insurance?
- It's not just the insurance.

217
00:13:35.825 --> 00:13:38.556
That's the straw that
broke the camel's back.

218
00:13:39.796 --> 00:13:42.561
Oh. so this is
about my condition.

219
00:13:42.832 --> 00:13:43.925
Look.

220
00:13:44.868 --> 00:13:46.461
Look.

221
00:13:48.471 --> 00:13:50.167
You see?

222
00:13:51.341 --> 00:13:52.934
See?

223
00:13:53.109 --> 00:13:55.078
I'm better.

224
00:13:55.345 --> 00:13:57.837
Howard. I'm fine.

225
00:14:01.184 --> 00:14:03.210
This is not what
"fine" looks like.

226
00:14:07.590 --> 00:14:09.889
Chuck. you are the best
legal mind I've ever known.

227
00:14:10.093 --> 00:14:11.959
Hands down.

228
00:14:12.362 --> 00:14:15.730
But your decision-making
has become unpredictable.

229
00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:21.028
I can't be partners with someone
whose judgment I don't trust.

230
00:14:25.542 --> 00:14:27.204
Chuck.

231
00:14:39.522 --> 00:14:44.324
This right here is the
Texas-New Mexico border.

232
00:14:44.494 --> 00:14:45.518
Now...

233
00:14:45.695 --> 00:14:48.426
all of my wells are square...

234
00:14:48.631 --> 00:14:50.725
on the Texas side.

235
00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:53.836
When I negotiated for the
mineral and property rights...

236
00:14:54.003 --> 00:14:57.371
the surveyor said that the
next nearest pool extended to...

237
00:15:02.245 --> 00:15:03.440
about here.

238
00:15:03.680 --> 00:15:05.080
Right.

239
00:15:05.248 --> 00:15:07.046
But after some extraction...

240
00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:09.776
the west wall of the
salt dome gave way...

241
00:15:09.953 --> 00:15:12.582
opening up another
pool that extends what?

242
00:15:12.756 --> 00:15:15.453
- A hundred yards over the border?
- About the size of it.

243
00:15:15.692 --> 00:15:18.924
And now you have the New
Mexico rights holders to deal with.

244
00:15:19.095 --> 00:15:20.723
They should get
profit on theirs...

245
00:15:20.897 --> 00:15:25.232
but I've got two states coming after
me for taxes on each and every gallon.

246
00:15:26.569 --> 00:15:28.561
No equipment crosses the border?

247
00:15:28.738 --> 00:15:30.263
No. ma'am.

248
00:15:30.440 --> 00:15:33.274
Nothing below the
surface. like the...?

249
00:15:33.810 --> 00:15:35.108
What. is it a drill bit?

250
00:15:35.311 --> 00:15:38.042
It'd be the sucker rod at this
point. but no. none of that.

251
00:15:38.214 --> 00:15:40.046
Only on the Texas side.

252
00:15:40.216 --> 00:15:43.778
That's not stopping New
Mexico from trying to bleed me.

253
00:15:43.953 --> 00:15:46.388
You said on the phone
you have a solution.

254
00:15:47.557 --> 00:15:49.753
You don't negotiate a
lease with the rights holders.

255
00:15:49.926 --> 00:15:52.259
- You offer to pay them damages.
- Damages?

256
00:15:52.429 --> 00:15:54.421
For diminishing their resource.

257
00:15:54.597 --> 00:15:58.056
A significant fraction of the
value of the New Mexico portion...

258
00:15:58.234 --> 00:16:00.726
but without paying for
the rights themselves.

259
00:16:00.904 --> 00:16:03.567
So kind of a payoff.

260
00:16:04.207 --> 00:16:05.732
You don't get
hit with the taxes.

261
00:16:05.942 --> 00:16:07.911
You think you can make that fly?

262
00:16:08.077 --> 00:16:10.603
If someone came
to me with this offer...

263
00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:12.408
I'd sure as hell take it.

264
00:16:12.582 --> 00:16:15.245
Wish I'd called you sooner.

265
00:16:15.618 --> 00:16:17.018
Way they're making noise...

266
00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:19.849
if I don't get this wrapped
up by the end of the quarter...

267
00:16:20.023 --> 00:16:22.583
I'm pretty sure the tax boys
are gonna take me apart.

268
00:16:23.359 --> 00:16:25.851
And that's two weeks from now?

269
00:16:28.131 --> 00:16:29.827
I can do it by then.

270
00:16:29.999 --> 00:16:31.126
Really?

271
00:16:31.301 --> 00:16:33.031
If we get the rights
holders in one place...

272
00:16:33.236 --> 00:16:35.967
I can walk them through
what we're proposing.

273
00:16:36.139 --> 00:16:39.007
- If they're smart. they'll go for it.
- Well. hot damn.

274
00:16:42.278 --> 00:16:44.873
Kevin said you're a miracle
worker. I didn't believe him.

275
00:16:45.114 --> 00:16:46.446
I'm starting to.

276
00:16:46.616 --> 00:16:49.814
Yeah. Well. let me work that
miracle first. then we'll talk.

277
00:16:49.986 --> 00:16:53.354
You know the way out of
here? I got a drill head...

278
00:16:53.523 --> 00:16:57.153
that's acting up on me out
in the north 40 I gotta check.

279
00:16:57.327 --> 00:16:58.818
Yeah. I'm good.

280
00:16:58.995 --> 00:17:01.965
You need anything from
me. you got my cell. Call me.

281
00:17:02.131 --> 00:17:03.793
Will do.

282
00:17:24.053 --> 00:17:25.715
Billy Gatwood meeting notes:

283
00:17:25.889 --> 00:17:27.050
Contact Gatwood Oil...

284
00:17:27.290 --> 00:17:29.987
get names and numbers for
New Mexico rights holders.

285
00:17:34.397 --> 00:17:36.866
Shit.

286
00:18:37.293 --> 00:18:39.319
No. no. no!

287
00:18:39.495 --> 00:18:40.861
Shit.

288
00:19:04.988 --> 00:19:08.356
Continuing notes from
Gatwood Oil meeting:

289
00:19:08.524 --> 00:19:10.618
Contact rights holders...

290
00:19:10.793 --> 00:19:12.193
begin scheduling.

291
00:19:36.219 --> 00:19:37.847
Howard.

292
00:19:40.023 --> 00:19:44.051
- What are you doing here. Jimmy?
- We have business to discuss.

293
00:19:44.227 --> 00:19:45.627
Is this about Chuck?

294
00:19:46.195 --> 00:19:47.424
Who?

295
00:19:48.064 --> 00:19:50.158
If you have business.
then call my secretary.

296
00:19:50.333 --> 00:19:52.996
I did. She stonewalled
me. as if you didn't know.

297
00:19:53.169 --> 00:19:54.169
Sandpiper.

298
00:19:54.704 --> 00:19:56.400
- What about it?
- It's time to settle.

299
00:19:56.572 --> 00:19:58.063
I saw the current offer.

300
00:19:58.241 --> 00:20:02.235
The clients make their losses
back. plus a solid chunk of change.

301
00:20:02.512 --> 00:20:04.344
Not that it's any
of your business...

302
00:20:04.514 --> 00:20:07.040
but we project a number
higher than the current offer.

303
00:20:07.216 --> 00:20:08.741
I get it. I get it.
You hold out...

304
00:20:08.951 --> 00:20:11.182
maybe you squeeze a
grand more for each client.

305
00:20:11.354 --> 00:20:13.983
Meanwhile. HHM nets
a few million. you know?

306
00:20:14.157 --> 00:20:16.422
You're screwing the
clients for your own benefit.

307
00:20:16.592 --> 00:20:19.255
Oh. so now you're
worried about the clients?

308
00:20:19.462 --> 00:20:21.397
It's the right thing to
do. and you know it.

309
00:20:21.564 --> 00:20:22.588
Please.

310
00:20:22.765 --> 00:20:25.394
All you care about is
your share of the payout.

311
00:20:26.769 --> 00:20:28.670
It's like talking to Gollum.

312
00:20:28.838 --> 00:20:32.172
You're transparent and pathetic.

313
00:20:33.109 --> 00:20:34.975
You want a handout?

314
00:20:36.412 --> 00:20:37.846
Here.

315
00:20:39.682 --> 00:20:40.682
Huh?

316
00:20:42.185 --> 00:20:43.881
Next time...

317
00:20:44.053 --> 00:20:45.578
why don't you bring a tin cup?

318
00:20:45.755 --> 00:20:47.747
It'd be more honest.

319
00:20:49.225 --> 00:20:50.591
Listen. Howard.

320
00:20:50.760 --> 00:20:53.355
Settle this now. It's in
everyone's best interests.

321
00:20:53.529 --> 00:20:55.623
Meaning it's in
your best interests.

322
00:20:55.798 --> 00:20:57.562
And if we don't. what
are you gonna do?

323
00:20:57.734 --> 00:21:00.636
Peel off members of the class.
leak insider info to Schweikart?

324
00:21:01.237 --> 00:21:02.261
Oh. I doubt it.

325
00:21:02.438 --> 00:21:05.306
I know you're low enough to do
that. but you're too damn greedy.

326
00:21:05.508 --> 00:21:08.603
You do any of that. you'll
be jeopardizing your payday.

327
00:21:10.079 --> 00:21:11.980
You'll get your damn money...

328
00:21:12.148 --> 00:21:14.083
you're just gonna
have to wait for it.

329
00:22:00.496 --> 00:22:02.658
What's so important?

330
00:22:02.865 --> 00:22:04.810
<i>Had a conversation...</i>

331
00:22:04.834 --> 00:22:06.325
<i>with our friend by the pool.</i>

332
00:22:06.502 --> 00:22:09.199
<i>He's very pleased
with our progress.</i>

333
00:22:09.372 --> 00:22:13.070
<i>He feels our consolidated
transportation method is working.</i>

334
00:22:14.177 --> 00:22:16.373
<i>In fact. it works so well...</i>

335
00:22:16.579 --> 00:22:21.677
<i>that our friend says this will be
the only way. moving forward.</i>

336
00:22:22.819 --> 00:22:25.948
<i>Of course. your territory
will stay yours forever.</i>

337
00:22:26.122 --> 00:22:29.991
<i>But this system has
less exposure. Less risk.</i>

338
00:22:30.526 --> 00:22:33.121
<i>Everything moves
through the Chilean.</i>

339
00:22:41.404 --> 00:22:42.872
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

340
00:22:49.812 --> 00:22:51.872
I hear you.

341
00:22:52.982 --> 00:22:54.075
Don Hector...

342
00:22:54.250 --> 00:22:56.810
I never asked for
this. I do not want it.

343
00:23:06.629 --> 00:23:07.756
Don Hector.

344
00:23:41.931 --> 00:23:45.527
Fuck Eladio...

345
00:23:45.701 --> 00:23:47.966
fuck Bolsa...

346
00:23:48.170 --> 00:23:50.230
and fuck you.

347
00:24:41.757 --> 00:24:45.819
Well. we go around about.
you know. six times. I think.

348
00:24:45.995 --> 00:24:47.623
I think we're... Yeah.

349
00:24:47.797 --> 00:24:49.595
I think... I think so.

350
00:24:51.667 --> 00:24:54.466
I know. It's just
so good for you.

351
00:24:54.637 --> 00:24:56.003
Hello. ladies.

352
00:24:56.238 --> 00:24:57.433
Good morning.

353
00:24:57.606 --> 00:24:59.040
- Jimmy?
- Hi. Jimmy.

354
00:24:59.241 --> 00:25:04.680
Jimmy. You girls go on a
little bit. I'll catch up with you.

355
00:25:06.048 --> 00:25:09.507
Wow. Irene. Fancy running
into you twice in one week.

356
00:25:09.685 --> 00:25:10.812
How lucky am I?

357
00:25:11.020 --> 00:25:13.615
You're a mall-walker?
I had no idea.

358
00:25:13.789 --> 00:25:16.054
Me? Oh. yeah. big-time.

359
00:25:16.258 --> 00:25:22.198
I mean. it's great for cardio.
hamstrings. glutes. IT band.

360
00:25:22.365 --> 00:25:25.335
I'm a huge mall-walker. Been
out of the game for a while.

361
00:25:25.501 --> 00:25:28.960
Developed this damn plantar
fasciitis. Hurts like a bear.

362
00:25:29.171 --> 00:25:31.572
Oh. I'm so sorry
to hear about that.

363
00:25:32.074 --> 00:25:35.704
Well. hey. I got
the cure right here.

364
00:25:36.545 --> 00:25:37.638
Pow!

365
00:25:37.813 --> 00:25:41.272
These have a special
gel and resistance coils...

366
00:25:41.484 --> 00:25:44.545
and a bunch of stuff. It's
like walking on pillows.

367
00:25:44.720 --> 00:25:47.747
Well. they look comfortable.

368
00:25:47.923 --> 00:25:49.016
You like them?

369
00:25:49.392 --> 00:25:52.294
Well. they...
They're quite stylish.

370
00:25:52.795 --> 00:25:54.491
Hey. you know what?

371
00:25:54.730 --> 00:25:58.497
I bought a pair for my girlfriend. and
they don't fit. and the store has this...

372
00:25:58.667 --> 00:26:01.193
- Wouldn't you know it?
- No-refunds policy.

373
00:26:01.404 --> 00:26:02.804
What size are you?

374
00:26:03.839 --> 00:26:07.105
Seven and a half.
seven and a half.

375
00:26:07.910 --> 00:26:10.846
Seven and a half.
Oh. there you go.

376
00:26:18.387 --> 00:26:20.253
- How does that feel?
- Oh...

377
00:26:22.691 --> 00:26:24.523
I... I see what you mean.

378
00:26:24.727 --> 00:26:29.358
They are so nice. and
they fit like a dream.

379
00:26:29.532 --> 00:26:31.933
But I can't take
these for free. Jimmy.

380
00:26:32.134 --> 00:26:33.864
Oh. please.

381
00:26:34.036 --> 00:26:37.973
- There is one thing you could do for me.
- What's that?

382
00:26:38.140 --> 00:26:40.132
Don't tell the other
folks I gave them to you.

383
00:26:40.342 --> 00:26:42.641
I don't wanna look like
I'm playing favorites.

384
00:26:42.845 --> 00:26:44.143
My lips are sealed.

385
00:26:44.346 --> 00:26:47.077
Then you enjoy those. I'm gonna
go get my heart rate back up.

386
00:26:47.249 --> 00:26:48.547
- Oh. thank you.
- See you later.

387
00:26:48.717 --> 00:26:51.118
Thank you so much. Jimmy.

388
00:27:00.096 --> 00:27:03.624
<i>The hand of love. Now. watch.
and I'll show you the story of life...</i>

389
00:27:03.866 --> 00:27:06.495
You've got some
questions. It's only natural.

390
00:27:06.669 --> 00:27:11.164
And the truth is. if Irene
settles. you'd get some money.

391
00:27:12.608 --> 00:27:15.442
But. I mean. it's not like
you guys need it. right?

392
00:27:16.645 --> 00:27:19.114
On the other hand. I did
get a look at their offer...

393
00:27:19.281 --> 00:27:22.615
and I don't wanna speak
out of school. but it's. uh:

394
00:27:24.687 --> 00:27:28.988
But. I mean. hey. everyone's
situation is different.

395
00:27:29.325 --> 00:27:31.760
Maybe Irene just
doesn't need the money.

396
00:27:31.961 --> 00:27:33.520
I don't know for a fact. but...

397
00:27:33.963 --> 00:27:36.797
when you see someone
buying nice new things...

398
00:27:36.966 --> 00:27:38.764
- Like those shoes.
- Like those shoes.

399
00:27:38.968 --> 00:27:40.129
Uh-huh.

400
00:27:41.170 --> 00:27:43.036
<i>Those must have
cost a pretty penny.</i>

401
00:27:43.272 --> 00:27:46.401
<i>If she can afford those.
she's walking on easy street.</i>

402
00:27:46.609 --> 00:27:49.340
And there's something else.

403
00:27:49.645 --> 00:27:51.045
You know. the lawyers?

404
00:27:51.280 --> 00:27:55.479
I mean. that's the lawyers'
share of the settlement...

405
00:27:55.651 --> 00:27:59.213
and your share
is this much. Doot.

406
00:27:59.421 --> 00:28:01.356
If Irene holds out...

407
00:28:01.524 --> 00:28:04.016
the lawyers get
this much more...

408
00:28:04.226 --> 00:28:06.786
and you are gonna
get this much more.

409
00:28:08.330 --> 00:28:10.162
Doesn't seem like
much difference.

410
00:28:10.366 --> 00:28:12.733
I know. but that's how it works.

411
00:28:12.968 --> 00:28:16.234
And Irene knows it too. I mean.
the lawyers have explained it to her.

412
00:28:17.072 --> 00:28:19.337
<i>It's crazy. but
it's all up to Irene.</i>

413
00:28:19.508 --> 00:28:22.205
<i>After all. she is the
class representative.</i>

414
00:28:22.378 --> 00:28:25.007
Does that mean
that she gets more?

415
00:28:25.181 --> 00:28:29.676
No. no. It just means in the
eyes of the court. she's special.

416
00:28:29.852 --> 00:28:32.879
She's like your
congressman or ambassador.

417
00:28:33.088 --> 00:28:34.852
Is there anything we can do?

418
00:28:35.024 --> 00:28:36.390
No.

419
00:28:36.559 --> 00:28:38.858
No. You can't do anything.

420
00:28:39.028 --> 00:28:41.190
I can't do anything.

421
00:28:41.564 --> 00:28:44.363
Only Irene.

422
00:28:45.868 --> 00:28:47.666
She probably knows what's best.

423
00:28:47.870 --> 00:28:50.840
I'm sure she's taking
your feelings into account.

424
00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:53.271
Hey. look at the big picture.

425
00:28:53.509 --> 00:28:56.104
Who needs money when
you got the moral high ground?

426
00:29:02.117 --> 00:29:03.415
Yoo-hoo!

427
00:29:03.886 --> 00:29:05.752
Rose.

428
00:29:06.121 --> 00:29:07.749
Helen.

429
00:29:08.724 --> 00:29:10.352
Ladies?

430
00:29:10.693 --> 00:29:12.889
Ladies?

431
00:29:54.970 --> 00:29:56.336
Ignacio?

432
00:29:56.805 --> 00:29:58.330
Hey. Dad.

433
00:29:59.475 --> 00:30:01.671
I was falling
asleep to the news.

434
00:30:02.645 --> 00:30:04.045
Yeah. I know.

435
00:30:05.848 --> 00:30:07.248
Are you all right. <i>mijo?</i>

436
00:30:17.660 --> 00:30:18.660
Dad...

437
00:30:21.297 --> 00:30:23.766
A man is going to
come to your shop. Soon.

438
00:30:24.433 --> 00:30:25.457
A bad man.

439
00:30:26.935 --> 00:30:27.935
What?

440
00:30:28.370 --> 00:30:31.204
He'll want to run
the place for a while.

441
00:30:32.107 --> 00:30:34.804
And you'll have to let him.

442
00:30:39.348 --> 00:30:40.873
Do you understand?

443
00:30:41.116 --> 00:30:43.176
And who is this man?

444
00:30:48.190 --> 00:30:49.818
Hector Salamanca.

445
00:30:53.629 --> 00:30:55.461
Salamanca.

446
00:30:57.199 --> 00:31:00.033
I've been working
for them again.

447
00:31:04.106 --> 00:31:06.701
I know what you're thinking.

448
00:31:06.875 --> 00:31:08.400
And you can scream at me...

449
00:31:08.610 --> 00:31:09.669
disown me...

450
00:31:09.845 --> 00:31:13.145
never speak to me again.
but whatever happens...

451
00:31:13.549 --> 00:31:15.245
you must do what he says.

452
00:31:17.119 --> 00:31:20.317
I know what you're
gonna want to do.

453
00:31:22.224 --> 00:31:23.886
But you can't.

454
00:31:25.694 --> 00:31:27.356
You can't. Dad.

455
00:31:27.629 --> 00:31:31.930
Do what he says. this will
blow over in a few weeks.

456
00:31:33.268 --> 00:31:35.396
If you don't...

457
00:31:37.339 --> 00:31:39.035
I swear.

458
00:31:39.408 --> 00:31:42.537
I swear it'll be over soon.

459
00:31:46.348 --> 00:31:48.943
How can I believe
anything you say?

460
00:31:50.452 --> 00:31:54.014
Promise me you won't
do anything stupid.

461
00:32:00.028 --> 00:32:02.588
Promise me. Dad.

462
00:32:04.600 --> 00:32:06.364
Please.

463
00:32:11.173 --> 00:32:13.438
Get out of my house.

464
00:32:57.519 --> 00:32:59.954
I'm still waiting for those
third-party subpoenas.

465
00:33:00.122 --> 00:33:02.751
- Great. Let me know. Thanks. Francis.
- All right.

466
00:33:02.958 --> 00:33:04.756
Julie. what's up?

467
00:33:04.927 --> 00:33:06.691
From Chuck. It
came via messenger.

468
00:33:06.862 --> 00:33:10.355
The instructions say he wants
you to read it as soon as possible.

469
00:33:14.036 --> 00:33:16.335
Uh. here's what I need
you to do: Call around.

470
00:33:16.505 --> 00:33:19.339
Find some place special
for the retirement party.

471
00:33:19.508 --> 00:33:22.945
Something classy. old
school. La Posada. maybe.

472
00:33:23.111 --> 00:33:25.603
And a band. something
jazzy. Upbeat.

473
00:33:26.248 --> 00:33:28.012
Find what's available.
Let's set it up.

474
00:33:28.183 --> 00:33:29.617
Okay.

475
00:33:42.998 --> 00:33:44.489
Goddamn it. Chuck.

476
00:33:47.202 --> 00:33:49.034
You're suing Hamlin
Hamlin McGill?

477
00:33:49.404 --> 00:33:51.202
Come on in. Howard.

478
00:33:54.576 --> 00:33:56.135
You turned the lights on?

479
00:33:56.311 --> 00:33:57.870
I told you.

480
00:33:58.046 --> 00:33:59.674
I'm back to normal.

481
00:34:00.048 --> 00:34:03.177
And. yes. I am suing
HHM for breach of contract.

482
00:34:03.352 --> 00:34:05.480
Do you have any
idea what you're doing?

483
00:34:05.654 --> 00:34:08.852
I believe I do. I'm
calling your bluff.

484
00:34:09.024 --> 00:34:11.721
This is my firm. I built it.

485
00:34:11.894 --> 00:34:15.160
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

486
00:34:15.364 --> 00:34:18.163
And you. I tutored
for the bar exam.

487
00:34:18.333 --> 00:34:19.562
You're not kicking me out.

488
00:34:19.868 --> 00:34:23.361
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say. so be it...

489
00:34:23.539 --> 00:34:26.031
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

490
00:34:26.241 --> 00:34:29.336
I believe that comes
to around $8 million.

491
00:34:29.511 --> 00:34:32.208
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

492
00:34:33.682 --> 00:34:35.913
You'd rather tear
down HHM than retire?

493
00:34:36.118 --> 00:34:39.088
You think I'm trouble
now as your partner?

494
00:34:39.254 --> 00:34:40.688
Imagine me as your enemy.

495
00:34:45.727 --> 00:34:47.127
Chuck.

496
00:34:48.063 --> 00:34:49.463
The damage you're going to do...

497
00:34:49.631 --> 00:34:53.090
If you'd like to discuss
this further. we can. in court.

498
00:34:53.869 --> 00:34:55.701
Until then...

